Idea: A not NSFW take on Succubi. Rather than being made by Khueen, they were instead made by Morgale on Lejos, specifically, in Outpost 3 / An-Tri'fhiana. They feast on memories by recreating and reenacting memories you had with people to overwrite themselves into those memories. For instance, if you had a partner that had a special way of holding your hand. If an Archubi starts holding your hand in that way, all the past memories you had of your partner holding your hand, are slowly replaced with the Archubi instead. Once overwritten, as you slowly forget that memory, that acts as them "digesting" the memory, feeding them and giving them sustinence. And, yes, they do not gain anything from forming new memories, they need to digest by overwriting pre-existing memories. However, 2 Archubi can overwrite each others' memories from one person over and over in an endless cycle (which some actually do, often without the person being aware. The AoS is highly against this practice, however... unless they're in control of it.) They do not do this willingly, it comes as naturally as humans digest food. Archubi cannot help overwriting memories.